---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SpecSection from "../components/SpecSection.astro";
---
<Layout
  title="TermCoder — pricing"
  description="TermCoder is free and open source for solo work. Pro unlocks hosting live rooms and classrooms — the host pays, joining is always free."
  active="pricing.html"
>
  <SpecSection gutter="//">
    <div class="t full">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> PRICING</div>
      <h2>Yours to build. Pro to lead.</h2>
      <p>The whole coding agent is free and open source, forever. Pro is for the person who runs a
        team or a class — and the people who join never pay.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="a full">
      <div class="price-grid">

        <div class="price-card">
          <div class="price-name">Free</div>
          <div class="price-amt"><span class="price-cur">$</span>0<span class="price-per"> / forever</span></div>
          <p class="price-sub">Everything one person needs.</p>
          <ul class="price-list">
            <li>The full coding agent — every model, agent, skill, memory, retrieval</li>
            <li>The study tutor for schoolwork</li>
            <li>Join any live room or classroom — unlimited, always free</li>
            <li>Desktop, CLI, and browser</li>
            <li>Open source, MIT</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="btn-2 go" href="download.html">Download the app</a>
        </div>

        <div class="price-card pro">
          <div class="price-tag">for teams &amp; classrooms</div>
          <div class="price-name">Pro</div>
          <div class="price-amt"><span class="price-cur">$</span>9<span class="price-per"> / month</span></div>
          <p class="price-sub">Host, teach, and sync. The host pays; joining stays free.</p>
          <ul class="price-list">
            <li>Everything in Free</li>
            <li>Host live rooms — voice, camera, screen share, more than one guest</li>
            <li>Run classrooms — teacher dashboard, assignments, submissions</li>
            <li>Sync your sessions across devices</li>
            <li>Support the project directly</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="btn-2 go" href="login.html">Get Pro</a>
          <p class="price-note">Checkout opens at launch. The app already activates license keys in
            Settings, so early teachers can start now — <a href="docs.html">ask for a key</a>.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>

  <SpecSection gutter="—">
    <div class="t full">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> WHY OPEN-CORE</div>
      <h2>The core stays open.</h2>
      <p>TermCoder is open source and the solo experience will always be free — no key, no account, no
        quota. Pro exists so teachers and teams can fund the project by paying for the collaboration they
        rely on, while their students and teammates join at no cost.</p>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>
</Layout>
